Package edu.common.dynamicextensions.domaininterface

Interface Summary
AbstractAttributeInterface This interface is extended by AssociationInterface and PrimitiveAttributeInterface.
AbstractMetadataInterface This is an interface extended by EntityInterface,EntityGroupInterface,AttributeInterface.This interface contains basic information needed for each metadata objects.
AssociationInterface This interface contains all the information regarding association between the entities.
AttributeInterface These are the attributes in the entities.
BooleanAttributeInterface This is a boolean type of primitive attribute.
BooleanValueInterface This object stores the permissible value of boolean type.This is a user defined value.
ByteArrayAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type byte array.This type of primitive attribute can be used for storing large amount of data such as image file or word file.
ByteArrayValueInterface This object stores the permissible value of type byte array.This is a user defined value.
CaDSRDEInterface The permissible values for an attribute may come from different sources such as caDSR or may be user defnied.
DataElementInterface Data element represent the source of the permissible values for a primitive attribute.
DateAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type date.
DateValueInterface This object stores the permissible value of date type.This is a user defined value.
DoubleAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type double.Using this information a coulmn of type double is prepared in the dynamically created tables.
DoubleValueInterface The permissible value of type double.
EntityGroupInterface Entities can be grouped in the form of entity goup.
EntityInterface Entity object stores information of the entity.For each entity a dynamic table is generated using the metadata information.
FloatAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type float.Using this information a column of type float is prepared.
FloatValueInterface The permissible value of type float.
IntegerAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type integar.Using this information a column of type integer is prepared.
IntegerValueInterface The permissible value of type integer.
LongAttributeInterface .
LongValueInterface The permissible value of type long.
PermissibleValueInterface When the value domain for an attribute is user defined,the data element object is of type CaDSRDE and this object contains a collection of permissible values.
RoleInterface For every entity association there are two roles invoved.They are source role and target role.
SemanticPropertyInterface For every abstract metadata object semantic properties are associated.
ShortAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type short.Using this information a column of type short is prepared.
ShortValueInterface The permissible value of type short.
StringAttributeInterface This is a primitive attribute of type String.Using this information a column of type string is prepared.
StringValueInterface The permissible value of type String.
UserDefinedDEInterface When the permissible values for an attribute are user defined the data element is of type UserDefinedDE.This type of data element contains collection of user defined permissible values.
